section.bdda-courses
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-6
        h2 Day 1 - BDD Fundamentals
        p We’ll start with a thorough introduction to BDD. The focus is on analysis and collaboration techniques. We’ll also give some demos of Cucumber to give you some context, but there won’t be any programming exercises.
        p We’ll teach you Example Mapping - a powerful technique we have developed to help business, IT and QA break requirements down into concrete examples. This exposes misunderstandings early and will help you write better executable specifications and automated tests later.
        h4 Learning outcomes
        ul.list-group
          li.list-group-item
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok-circle
            |  The fundamental principles and practices of BDD
          li.list-group-item
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok-circle
            |  The importance of Rules and Examples
          li.list-group-item
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok-circle
            |  Translating examples into Gherkin - Cucumber’s format for executable specifications
          li.list-group-item
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok-circle
            |  Conversation patterns for discovering edge cases
          li.list-group-item
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok-circle
            |  The importance of a ubiquitous language for problems and solutions
          li.list-group-item
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok-circle
            |  Using Example Mapping and Discovery Workshops to achieve shared understanding
          li.list-group-item
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok-circle
            |  Roles and responsibilities on a BDD team
      .col-md-6
        h2 Day 2 - Discovery Workshops
        p We’ll be working on a case study (a system to manage a public library), and you will spend the day analysing and breaking down user stories into examples.
        p You’ll be running your own Discovery Workshops, practicing the Example Mapping technique you learned on day 1.
        p You’ll experience how easy it can be to bring everyone’s understanding of requirements to the same level. You’ll also learn simple techniques to detect when there are too many unknowns to proceed with development.
        p You’ll learn you how you can get started with the collaborative analysis techniques of BDD without changing your existing process or organisational structure.
